23/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Interior Minister Besir Atalay said on Saturday (August 22nd) that Turkey has made significant progress in settling the Kurdish issue through the new government initiative. Atalay's statement followed his meeting with NGO representatives. "We believe that we will find a solution to the [Kurdish] problem through democratic measures, efforts and compromise. I believe that we have made big progress in this process," he said. Atalay refused to comment on the opposition's criticism regarding the government initiative. (Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, Trend - 22/08/09)
